                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/834: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-17T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received December 17—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>123. Drummond telephoned this morning that during Lugano session the three powers
                    mostly interested, namely Great Britain, France and Germany, agreed to advise
                    Loudon to call meeting of the Preparatory Commission between the 8th and 15th of
                    April (the latest date to which Stresemann<note n="30" xml:id="d227fn30">Gustav
                        Stresemann, German Minister of Foreign Affairs.</note> would agree).
                    Drummond stated that the date was not made definite since they recognized that
                    the members <pb facs="0392" n="264" xml:id="pg_264"/> of the American delegation
                    coming from the United States might desire to remain home over Easter which
                    occurs March 31. He asked me to obtain an unofficial expression of opinion from
                    you as to which time would be most convenient for the opening of the session
                    between these dates.</p>
                <p>Copy to Gibson.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
